```json
{
  "framing": [
    "The proposal is architecturally directional but quantitatively under-scaled: a Rs 5 Cr sleeve funded by fresh inflow grows the corpus additively yet leaves equity at 78.5 percent against a 70 percent ceiling and debt at 12.7 percent against a 20 percent floor. The Risk Assessor's most consequential observations cluster in three places — the residual mandate breach (G1 requires_clarification), the tax-amplified yield asymmetry inside the sleeve under the post-July 2024 debt MF regime, and the unresolved Direct-versus-Regular plan question over a 7-year horizon. Counterfactual analysis therefore concentrates on sizing, intra-sleeve mix, and execution-gate alternatives rather than on rejecting the architectural intent, which all activated evidence agents support.",
    "Three of the alternatives below are tax- and regulation-aware in the sense the Indian Context block permits. The slab-rate treatment of debt MF gains (Budget 2024 change, cited by E7) and the section 10(15)(iv)(h) exemption on the NHAI/REC/PFC ladder create a structural after-tax wedge at the investor's likely surcharge-inclusive tier of 35-42.7 percent; this is the quantitative basis for re-weighting the intra-sleeve mix toward tax-free bonds. The str_001 structure-fit flag is indicative reference data, not a SEBI prohibition, and is treated as a pre-execution clarification gate rather than as a path-defining constraint. No path below relies on a tax-matrix or surcharge-band entry that did not match the proposal.",
    "The Reliance concentration (20.3 percent of liquid corpus) and the meta-wealth conditioning from the Rs 165 Cr private company stake are flagged by E4 and the Risk Assessor as out-of-scope for this proposal but in-scope for sequencing. Two paths below address whether the band breach is resolved by scaling debt up, by trimming equity outside the Reliance line, or by accepting the residual as intentional headroom — a choice that belongs to the investor and advisor jointly rather than to the engine."
  ],
  "alternative_paths": [
    {
      "label": "Scaled debt deployment to Rs 8-9 Cr to close the band breach",
      "description": "Lift the sleeve from Rs 5 Cr to approximately Rs 8.5 Cr (24-25 percent of liquid AUM) so post-action debt sits at or near the 20 percent floor and equity moves materially closer to the 70 percent ceiling. Addresses the residual mandate breach risk directly; requires either additional fresh inflow timing or a partial trim of a diversified equity MF position outside the Reliance line."
    },
    {
      "label": "Intra-sleeve re-weighting toward tax-free bonds",
      "description": "Within the same Rs 5 Cr envelope, route Rs 3.0-3.5 Cr to the NHAI/REC/PFC tax-free ladder (interest exempt u/s 10(15)(iv)(h)) and Rs 1.5-2.0 Cr to the short-duration debt MF, dropping or shrinking the AAA corporate bond MF tranche. Addresses the tax-amplified yield asymmetry risk at the investor's 35-42.7 percent effective surcharge-inclusive tier, where debt MF slab-rate taxation post-July 2024 materially compresses after-tax yield versus the tax-free coupon."
    },
    {
      "label": "Sequenced deployment with equity trim in tranche two",
      "description": "Execute Rs 5 Cr now as proposed; commit in the case file to a second tranche within 12-18 months that combines a further Rs 3-4 Cr debt addition with a Rs 2-3 Cr trim of one diversified equity MF position (Reliance held by design). Addresses both the residual mandate breach and the concentrated-position non-action pattern by sequencing rather than deferring."
    },
    {
      "label": "Direct-plan and structure-fit gate before deployment",
      "description": "Hold execution until two pre-trade items are closed: written confirmation that the Kotak scheme is being purchased under the Direct plan (resolving the 30-60 bps TER ambiguity that compounds to 3-4 percent over seven years), and advisor sign-off on the str_001 mutual_fund_debt eligibility note for individual/resident. Addresses the Direct-versus-Regular and structure-eligibility risks as gates rather than as post-trade checks."
    },
    {
      "label": "Staged entry across the yield-curve volatility window",
      "description": "Deploy the Rs 3 Cr MF portion in two or three tranches over 60-90 days rather than as a single lot, given the 10Y intraday spike to 7.19 percent on April 3 and active crude/FII volatility; the Rs 2 Cr tax-free bond ladder is laddered on its own coupon and maturity logic. Addresses the yield-curve mark-to-market and monsoon-driven rate-path delay risks by spreading the entry point rather than concentrating it at a single mark."
    }
  ]
